      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ZIPPING MIGALOO (1) broke well and quickly mustered speed to win over the 400m at Gawler two runs back then settled forward again when finishing second at Gawler last start. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card last start despite being beaten. Likely to feature again. TOWN STRANGER (2) produced an impressive win last time in quickest of the meeting when scoring by 1.75 lengths (30.67) at Gawler. Speedy runner and should be in the action early from an inside box. Can measure up again. PAW SHAYNA (4) broke from a low draw and filled a minor placing last start, beaten only half a length (30.69) behind Aunty Meeka at Broken Hill. Ran one of the fastest times on the program last start despite finishing in the minors. Will give a great sight again. FEDERAL LADY (8) looks an each-way chance.",
